    narr:narration """Grammar and syntax observations of Scarlet's writing converge on a few load-bearing habits. Voice is overwhelmingly [active and agent-first](narr:StyleObs_10), first-person declarative, with [active constructions dominating and passive voice rare](narr:StyleObs_9). Rhythm runs on [deliberate alternation](narr:StyleObs_9) — long explanatory sentence then short punchy verdict — and on [parallel/tricolon structures](narr:StyleObs_6) and [punchy section-anchor declaratives](narr:StyleObs_6). At the micro level a recurring pattern dominates: [bold lead-phrase + colon + elaboration](narr:StyleObs_10), extended into [bold-labeled data-source bullets](narr:StyleObs_BoldBulletStructure), [bulleted failure-mode incident reports](narr:StyleObs_BulletedFailureModeStructure), and [imperative-mood numbered lists](narr:StyleObs_ImperativeNumberedList). A distinct technical register surfaces in [arrow notation for sequential flows](narr:StyleObs_ArrowFlowNotation), [arrow-linked parallel verb phrases](narr:StyleObs_ArrowParallelism), and a [three-column pedagogical classification table](narr:StyleObs_TableClassification). Idiolect markers — coined compound nouns and OS/mechanical metaphors — recur as a signature ([compression anxiety, one-shot](narr:StyleObs_10); [bootload a worldview, opinion machine](narr:StyleObs_6); [escape valve, arrow/archery](narr:StyleObs_5)).""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_10> ;
